{
  "text": "In a small bowel transplantation model [CITATION_1] , supplemental glutamine (a) improved intestinal morphology; and (c) improved intestinal monosaccharide absorption. In experimental sepsis [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Kaneko et al. 1993; [CITATION_5] , supplemental glutamine (a) improved intestinal morphology; (b) increased intestinal mucosal protein content ; (c) increased mucosal glutaminase (EC 3.5.1.2) activity and reduced bacterial translocation; and ( d ) improved survival. In a rat abdominal radiation model [CITATION_6] , glutamine supplementation had no effect on (a) intestinal morphology; and (b) mucosal DNA content.",
